               development has not been well studied because of their transient
               nature and paucity of molecular markers. We have used markers of
               pre-placodal ectoderm (PPE) (six1, eya1) to determine that
               gradients of both neural inducers and anteroposterior signals are
               necessary to induce and appropriately position the PPE.
