  number    =  20,
  pages     = "5461--5473",
  abstract  = "The medial telencephalon is a source of neurons that follow
               distinct tangential trajectories of migration to various
               structures such as the cerebral cortex, striatum, and olfactory
               bulb. In the present study, we characterized the forebrain
               anomalies in Zic1/Zic3 compound mutant mice. Zic1 and Zic3 were
