  volume    =  3,
  number    =  4,
  pages     = "1140--1152",
  abstract  = "Melanocytes are pigment-producing cells of neural crest (NC)
               origin that are responsible for protecting the skin against UV
               irradiation. Pluripotent stem cell (PSC) technology offers a
               promising approach for studying human melanocyte development and
               disease. Here, we report that timed exposure to activators of
