               signal-related genes, Col1A1, Col1A2, and increased MMP2
               transcripts compared with those from wild-type. Our data strongly
               support the hypothesis that a reduction of CRABP-II expression
               accelerates and promotes skin aging, and suggest CRABP-II as a
               novel target to improve the efficacy of retinoid-mediated
               anti-aging therapies.",
