  author    = "Jahoda, C A and Horne, K A and Oliver, R F",
  journal   = "Nature",
  publisher = "Springer Science and Business Media LLC",
  volume    =  311,
  number    =  5986,
  pages     = "560--562",
  abstract  = "Mammalian hairs are formed by differentiation and keratinization
               of cells produced in the epidermal matrix (Figs 3, 4). Using the
               rodent vibrissa follicle as a model, transplantation studies have
               shown that the dermal papilla, a discrete population of
               specialized fibroblasts, is of prime importance in the growth of
